    <!-- ARCore unsupported-device dialog. Triggered when
         ArCoreApk.checkAvailability returns
         UNSUPPORTED_DEVICE_NOT_CAPABLE — almost always because
         the user\'s Google Play Services for AR is too old to
         know about their phone (the device-support list lives
         in that APK, not in our SDK pin). -->
    <string name="arcore_unsupported_title">ARCore reports unsupported</string>
    <string name="arcore_unsupported_body">Your phone hardware should support ARCore, but the system component that gates it (\"Google Play Services for AR\") is reporting otherwise. This usually means it\'s missing or out of date — its bundled device list is what tells ARCore which phones are capable, and a copy from before your phone\'s launch won\'t recognize it.\n\nTap \"Open Play Store\" to install or update Google Play Services for AR, then come back to this screen and try again.</string>
